add_word(&development, "Stovepipe", "A system that has the potential to share data or functionality with other systems but which does not.");
add_word(&development, "The Cathedral model", "The source code is available with each software release, but code developed between releases is restricted to an exclusive group of developers.");
add_word(&development, "The Bazaar model", "The source code is developed over the Internet in view of the public.");
add_word(&development, "XY Problem", "You want to do X, and you think Y is the best way of doing so. Instead of asking about X, you ask about Y.");
add_word(&development, "Second System Effect", "The tendency of small, elegant, and successful systems, to be succeeded by over-engineered, bloated systems, due to inflated expectations and overconfidence.");
add_word(&development, "Benevolent Dictator For Life", "A open-source software development practice where project founders retain the final say in disputes or arguments within the community.");
add_word(&development, "Yak Shaving", "Refers to a task, that leads you to perform another related task and so on, and so on — all distracting you from your original goal.");
